channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "My favorite money hack of all is using Airbnb to hack rent. I mean think about how much your rent is every month. For most people it's like half of their income. So if you can just eliminate that expense, you can invest in yourself, you could travel, you could learn something new, you could invest in property or other passive income generating streams, there's so much you can do with an extra $1,500, $2,000, $3,000 a month that most people pay in rent. Anyone can put their place on Airbnb. Some places are gonna do better than others. If you own the place then it's easy, you can just do it. If you rent the place, you need permission from your landlord. You're young, you're single or just a couple and you guys want to travel and you know you're gonna be out of town for a while or you want to take like a six-month vacation, that's the best time to Airbnb because otherwise your house is gonna be sitting there empty, costing you money every month, and you're not getting anything from that. When I'm Airbnbing my place, I'm typically traveling or I'm staying with friends, but usually traveling. Traveling is amazing. A lot of people never travel from their hometown and that's just crazy to me because there's so much out there, especially in terms of dating. If you're a young guy and you want to get out there and see what kind of women you're into, who you like, get out of the U.S. Go to Eastern Europe, go to Brazil. Last summer I was in Eastern Europe for almost three months and I made enough money subletting my place that my entire trip was free and it paid for my rent. People say, I don't have the money to travel. Bullshit. You don't have the money to not travel.
